{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/appbackend\/runmainloop(_:)"]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"externalID":"s:12SwiftCrossUI10AppBackendP11runMainLoopyyyyScMYccF","required":true,"symbolKind":"method","title":"runMainLoop(_:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"runMainLoop"},{"kind":"text","text":"(() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida","text":"Void"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","remoteSource":{"fileName":"AppBackend.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/stackotter\/swift-cross-ui\/blob\/main\/Sources\/SwiftCrossUI\/Backend\/AppBackend.swift#L128"},"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"SwiftCrossUI"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppBackend"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppBackend\/runMainLoop(_:)"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Often in UI frameworks (such as Gtk), code is run in a callback"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"after starting the app, and hence this generic root window creation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"API must reflect that. This is always the first method to be called"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and is where boilerplate app setup should happen."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"runMainLoop"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"callback"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"@escaping"},{"kind":"text","text":" @"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"kind":"text","text":" () -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Void","preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Runs the backend’s main run loop. The app will exit when this method","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"returns. This wall always be the first method called by SwiftCrossUI.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The callback is where SwiftCrossUI will create windows, render"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"initial views, start state handlers, etc. The setup action must be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"run exactly once. The backend must be fully functional before the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"callback is ready."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is up to the backend to decide whether the callback runs before or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"after the main loop starts. For example, some backends such as the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AppKit"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"backend can create windows and widgets before the run loop starts, so it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"makes the most sense to run the setup before the main run loop starts (it’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"also not possible to run the setup function once the main run loop starts","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"anyway). On the other side is the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk"},{"text":" backend which must be on the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"main loop to create windows and widgets (because otherwise the root","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"window has not yet been created, which is essential in Gtk), so the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"setup function is passed to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk"},{"text":" as a callback to run once the main","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"run loop starts.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://SwiftCrossUI/documentation/SwiftCrossUI/AppBackend/runMainLoop(_:)":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"runMainLoop(_:)","required":true,"url":"\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/appbackend\/runmainloop(_:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppBackend\/runMainLoop(_:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Often in UI frameworks (such as Gtk), code is run in a callback"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"after starting the app, and hence this generic root window creation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"API must reflect that. This is always the first method to be called"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and is where boilerplate app setup should happen."}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"runMainLoop"},{"kind":"text","text":"(() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida","text":"Void"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}]},"doc://SwiftCrossUI/documentation/SwiftCrossUI":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create cross-platform desktop apps for macOS, Linux, Windows, iOS and tvOS."}],"role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI","url":"\/documentation\/swiftcrossui","title":"SwiftCrossUI","kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftCrossUI/documentation/SwiftCrossUI/AppBackend":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AppBackend","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppBackend","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A backend that can be used to run an app. Usually built on top of an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"existing UI framework."}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/appbackend","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AppBackend","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"AppBackend","type":"topic"}}}